Perl DEPENDENCIES:
==================

CentOS / RHEL
-------------

for a base CentOS / Red Hat 6 machine without EPEL enabled, get the following packages from EPEL:

http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/perl-Crypt-RC4-2.02-1.el6.noarch.rpm
http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/perl-Digest-Perl-MD5-1.8-2.el6.noarch.rpm
http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/perl-Jcode-2.07-1.el6.noarch.rpm
http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/perl-OLE-Storage_Lite-0.19-2.el6.noarch.rpm
http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/perl-Spreadsheet-ParseExcel-0.5900-1.el6.x86_64.rpm
http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/perl-Spreadsheet-WriteExcel-2.37-1.el6.noarch.rpm
http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/perl-Spreadsheet-XLSX-0.13-3.el6.noarch.rpm
http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/perl-Unicode-Map-0.112-12.el6.x86_64.rpm


additionally, install the following one using yum:

yum install perl-Text-Iconv


Mac OSX
-------

If you want to run this script directly on your Mac computer, there is an easy way to install perl 
modules via cpan or cpanm. You can install cpanm using homebrew: http://brew.sh

# brew install cpanminus

# cpanm Spreadsheat::XLSX
# cpanm use Text::Iconv;

... and any other Perl modules that may be missing.



Windows
-------

Find out yourself and give me feedback.